  "topic": "Pipes and Text Processing",
  "slides": [
    {
      "slideId": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "value": "What Are Pipes and Text Processing?"
        },
        {
          "type": "definition",
          "value": "A pipe | connects the output of one command to the input of another. Text processing tools like sort, awk, and sed help filter, format, and modify text."
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Think of pipes like plumbing: water flows through pipes and gets processed by filters. In Linux, data flows through commands the same way."
        },
        {
          "type": "table",
          "value": [
            ["Tool / Symbol", "Purpose"],
            ["| (pipe)", "Connects commands together"],
            ["sort", "Sorts lines alphabetically or numerically"],
            ["awk", "Extracts columns and formats text"],
            ["sed", "Edits text on the fly (search/replace)"],
            ["grep", "Filters lines by matching patterns"]
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "value": "Use pipes to build powerful command chains — no files or editors needed!"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "slideId": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "value": "Using Pipes ( | ) to Combine Commands"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Pipes send the output of one command directly into the next command as input."
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "command": "ls | sort",
          "description": "Lists files and sorts them alphabetically."
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "command": "cat data.txt | grep apple",
          "description": "Shows only lines containing the word 'apple'."
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "command": "ps aux | grep firefox",
          "description": "Finds processes related to 'firefox'. Useful for troubleshooting."
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "value": "Rule: Left side sends data → right side processes it."
        }
      ],
      "video": {
        "platform": "youtube",
        "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7PjAXqTPYPg"
      }
    },
    {
      "slideId": 3,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "value": "Text Processing Tools (sort, awk, sed)"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "These tools help format, filter, and transform text directly in the terminal."
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "command": "sort numbers.txt",
          "description": "Sorts text alphabetically or by number."
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "command": "awk '{print $1, $3}' users.txt",
          "description": "Prints the 1st and 3rd column from a file (useful for data extraction)."
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "command": "sed 's/apple/orange/g' fruits.txt",
          "description": "Replaces the word 'apple' with 'orange' everywhere."
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "value": "awk works like a column picker, sed works like search/replace."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "slideId": 4,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "value": "Combining Everything Together"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "command": "cat data.txt | grep error | sort | uniq",
          "description": "Finds error lines, sorts them, removes duplicates — great for logs."
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "command": "ps aux | grep nginx | awk '{print $2}'",
          "description": "Find nginx processes and show only their process IDs."
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "command": "dmesg | tail -20 | grep fail",
          "description": "Check recent system errors containing 'fail'."
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "value": "Start with simple pipes and add new commands step by step."
        }
      ],
      "video": {
